						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: ⎯⎯ Year: Śaka 1425, <hi rend="italic">Rudhirōdgarin Mṛigasīrisha śu. 2.</hi></hi></p>						

						<p>Impression of this inscription is missing and only the transcript is available.</p>						

						<p>Records that Tirumalai-Nāyakkar, Īśvara-Nāyakkar, Viśvēśvaraśivāchārya, and administrator of the temple gave a deed <hi rend="italic">(kaiyyōlai)</hi> at the temple in Dēvakkapuram to Samarapuṅgava-Dīkshitar of <hi rend="italic">Ātrēya-gōtra</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Āpasthambha-sūtra</hi>, conveying the gift of seven hundred <hi rend="italic">kuḻi</hi> of dry land, sixty <hi rend="italic">kuḻi</hi> (of wet land ?), a house measuring sixty feet with all appertenances at the village, Kailāsam, for the merit of the king <hi rend="italic">(svāmi)</hi> Narasa-Nāyaka, who attained <hi rend="italic">Śivalōkaprāpti</hi> (died).</p>						

						</summary>
